revision.text:
'''Shidori Shrine''' (倭文神社) refers to Shinto shrines bearing the name "Shidori" (also read as Shizuri, Shitori, or Shidori).
These shrines enshrine '''{{ill|Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|1=Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|zh|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (also known as '''Amenohaikazuchi-no-Mikoto''', '''Ameno Hachio''', or '''Takehatsuchi''') as the '''deity of weaving''', alongside '''{{ill|Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|ja|天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (also known as '''Amano Yachichihime''' or '''Amanoorihime'''). These shrines were established by the '''{{ill|Shizuri clan|ja|倭文部|1=Shizuri clan|2=ja|3=倭文氏|4=zh|5=倭文氏|6=de|7=Shizuri Clan|8=fr|9=Clan Shizuri|lt=Shizuri Bemin (vassals of the Shizuri clan)|lt=Shizuri clan|12=draft|12=draft}}''', who worshipped Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto as their ancestral deity.
The '''origin of these shrines is attributed to''' the '''{{ill|Katsuragi Shitori niimasu Amenohaikazuchi no Mikoto Shrine|ja|葛木倭文座天羽雷命神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' in '''Katsuragi, Nara Prefecture'''. However, while the introduction and promotion of silk weaving technology in Japan is credited to '''{{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}''', some Shidori Shrines claim their origins date back to the reign of '''{{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}'''. Therefore, these shrines provide '''important historical evidence''' regarding '''when and where silk weaving developed in Japan (Wa).'''
Additionally, in the '''2016 animated film "[[:en:Your_Name|Your Name]]"''', the fictional '''{{ill|Miyamizu Shrine|ja|宮水神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' is depicted as enshrining '''Shidori deity Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto (倭文神建葉槌命)'''
== Shizuri Shrines of the Engishiki ==
*'''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Isesaki)|ja|倭文神社 (伊勢崎市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Shidori-go, Nanba District, Kōzuke Province''' – (Higashi-Kaminomiya-cho, {{ill|Isesaki, Gunma|ja|伊勢崎市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Gunma Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shizu Shrine|ja|静神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (静神社)''' in '''Kuji District, Hitachi Province''' – ({{ill|Naka, Ibaraki|ja|那珂市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)|ja|倭文神社 (韮崎市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Koma District, Kai Province''' – (Miyakubo, {{ill|Nirasaki, Yamanashi|ja|韮崎市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Yamanashi Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Fujinomiya)|ja|倭文神社 (富士宮市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Fuji District, Suruga Province''' – (Hoshiyama, {{ill|Fujinomiya, Shizuoka|ja|富士宮市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Shizuoka Prefecture]]) * '''Shidori Shrine (倭文神社)''' in '''Tagata District, Izu Province''' – Identified with multiple candidate shrines, including '''{{ill|Kuwado Shrine|ja|鍬戸神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' ({{ill|Mishima, Shizuoka|ja|三島市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Shizuoka Prefecture]]) * '''Shidori Shrine (倭文神社)''' in '''Suzuka District, Ise Province''' – '''{{ill|Kasado Shrine|ja|加佐登神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (merged into [[Suzuka, Mie|Suzuka]], [[Mie Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Maizuru)|ja|倭文神社 (舞鶴市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Kasa District, Tango Province''' – (Imada, {{ill|Maizuru, Kyoto|ja|舞鶴市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Kyoto Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Yosano)|ja|倭文神社 (与謝野町)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Yosa District, Tango Province''' – (Mikawachi, {{ill|Yosano, Kyoto|ja|与謝野町|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Kyoto Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Asago)|ja|倭文神社 (朝来市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Asago District, Tajima Province''' – (Maruyama, {{ill|Asago, Hyogo|ja|朝来市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Hyogo Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Tottori)|ja|倭文神社 (鳥取市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Takakusa District, Inaba Province''' – (Shidori, {{ill|Tottori, Tottori|ja|鳥取市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Tottori Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shitori Shrine (Tottori)|ja|倭文神社 (湯梨浜町)|1=Shitori Shrine (Tottori)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Kawamura District, Hōki Province''' – (Miyauchi, {{ill|Yurihama, Tottori|ja|湯梨浜町|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Tottori Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Kurayoshi)|ja|倭文神社 (倉吉市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Kume District, Hōki Province''' – (Shizu, {{ill|Kurayoshi, Tottori|ja|倉吉市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Tottori Prefecture]])
== Other shrines == *'''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Tono)|ja|倭文神社 (遠野市)|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (Tsuchibuchi-cho, {{ill|Tono, Iwate|ja|遠野市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Iwate Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Nara)|ja|倭文神社 (奈良市)|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (Nishikujo-cho, {{ill|Nara, Nara|ja|奈良市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Nara Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Tsuyama)|ja|倭文神社 (津山市油木北)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Shidori-go, Kume District, Mimasaka Province''' – (Yukikita, {{ill|Tsuyama, Okayama|ja|津山市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Okayama Prefecture]]) * '''{{ill|Shidori Shrine (Awaji)|ja|倭文神社 (あわじ市倭文委文)|12=draft|12=draft}} (倭文神社)''' in '''Shidori-go, Mihara District, Awaji Province''' – (Shidori, {{ill|Minamiawaji, Hyogo|ja|南あわじ市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Hyogo Prefecture]])
Additionally, '''{{ill|Ōmika Shrine|8=ja|9=大甕神社|ja|大甕神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' ({{ill|Hitachi, Ibaraki|ja|日立市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]) also enshrines '''Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto'''. Similarly, '''{{ill|Ishii Shrine|ja|石井神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' ({{ill|Kasama, Ibaraki|ja|笠間市|12=draft|12=draft}}, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]) enshrines the same deity, with a large sacred rock called "Mitarai" located to the south. == See Also ==
* '''{{ill|Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|1=Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|zh|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|1=Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|zh|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (also known as Amenohaikazuchi-no-Mikoto) * '''{{ill|Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|ja|天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|lt=Ame-no-Tanabatahime|1=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=天棚機姫神|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|4=de|5=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|6=fr|7=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|8=zh|9=天棚機姫神|10=nl|11=Tanabatabime-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (also known as Amanoorihime)
